						<div class="postbody">Congrats! You now have something that not many games do, a clean split.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">exdeath wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Then my next question is, is there a diagram of the entire horizonal sweep with dot timing?</div><br />I don't think so, but that would be cool to have.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Is is 341 dots per line where 0-255 is the active line or...?</div><br />There are definitely 341 PPU clock cycles in one scanline, but I think <s>they are typically numbered 1-341 rather than 0-340. That would make the visible portion 1-256</s>, the rest is HBlank.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">How long does a CHR-ROM bank switch take with MMC3?</div><br />Bankswitching is instantaneous.<br /><br />EDIT: Nintendulator appears to number cycles starting from 0.</div>

					
